value.0: I welcome you into the ShadowGuard, my <brother/sister>...
Would you like some help in your mission?
As you wish.
Very good, <mister/missus> <LastName>
<< Activates "N_TALK_SWITCH" if "N_MODULE_STAGE" is 9. USING THIS FOR TESTING AT THE MOMENT! >>
Welcome into our order, <FirstName>...
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_ST_2_MAIN" >>
<< Activates "N_TALK_SWITCH" if "N_MODULE_STAGE" is 2. >>
Please do speak with Overlord Vhorkas, <FirstName>, so we may escape this city... I do not know how much longer I can take the cries of this city's dead spirits.
Now is not the time for words, <FirstName>. We have to escape this city at once!
The Crimson Prophet is far more powerful than we had imagined... Speak with Markius, <FirstName>. We must find a way out of this doomed city soon...
Akhana take you!
Be wary, <FirstName>... The Crimson Prophet is not a foe to be trifled with...
Shall I accompany you to the Docks, <FirstName>?
As you wish, <FirstName>, but do be careful. Ghaarak is not a safe place at the moment...
So much death in this city... Please do speak with Markius. He has a matter to discuss with you that may well concern your safety.
<StartAction>[This beautiful Elven maiden gives you a charming smile as you approach.]</Start>
<StartAction>[Kara turns her dark eyes towards you.]</Start> So, it seems we meet again, <lad/lass>...
Greetings to you. I am Kara Dy'nesh. I am pleased to meet your acquaintance.
As you like. Should you wish to speak to me further, you may find me here.
Do you wish for me to join you on the trip to the docks? I am a priestess of no small skill, and may prove valuable to you.
Then lead the way, <FirstName>, and I shall follow.
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_ST_1_MAIN" >>
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_PREL_KARA" >>
So much death in this city... Please do speak with Markius. He has a matter to discuss with you that may well concern your safety.

<StartAction>[Kara Dy'nesh, the sultry Elven beauty of the ShadowGuard, stands before some sort of ritual table as you approach. She turns her large, soft eyes towards you.]</Start> Greetings, <FirstName>.
What may I do for you today, <FirstName>?
<StartAction>[Kara nods.]</Start> Farewell, <FirstName>. <StartAction>[With that, Kara returns to her affairs, and does not seem to pay you any more heed...]</Start>
<StartAction>[Kara gazes down for a moment, as though recalling a troublesome memory.]</Start> The Final Initiation... yes, I remember it well...

You must beware the trappings of that trial, <FirstName>, for it can be fraught with danger. It is a placed created by the strongest sorceries Rakha can conjure, and it will test you physically, mentally, and spiritually.
Remember that the Almighty Rakha can see through flesh and soul, and He shall test you in the way He sees fit. Remain true to yourself, though, and you should do just fine.
<StartAction>[Sigh.]</Start> I'm not much of one for gossip, but ask your questions, and I shall answer them as I may...
Vhorkas has been good to all of us in the ShadowGuard, aiding us in reward for our service to the Empire. He can take you far, so long as you do his bidding.
Make no mistake about it, however. Vhorkas serves Emperor Rakha fully, and his kindness extends only so far as that. Vhorkas does the Empire's bidding, and no one else's...
Tarin can be quite the troublemaker when he sets his mind to it, always up to some sort of foolishness. And his affection for the card tables has always been his biggest downfall...
The Halfling does have a wide knowledge of the Northern Reaches, however, and he seems to have friends everywhere. I suppose there are some perks to being addicted to the gaming tables...
Markius is a mystery to us all, perhaps even to himself. He clouds his personal life in as much secrecy as he does his physical form while scouting for the ShadowGuard.
I will say there are few who can match his deadliness from the cover of shadow, however. He has saved the ShadowGuard more than once, and his usefulness to us can not be overstated...
Markius is a good man, I suppose, but he has shackled himself within the laws of Emperor Rakha. His heart will never be his own, for he shall forever be nothing more than Rakha's pawn...

Still, as leaders go, we could have a far worse one than he. Markius has never led us astray in our missions, and none can doubt his courage in the heat of battle. I cannot say I would die for him, but I gladly stand at his side...

<StartAction>[Kara gives you a scathing glance.]</Start> And why should I tell you of it? After all, you were the one who kept me from retrieving the Bloodstone... the most important ingredient of this ritual!
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> Your excuses do little to ease my anger, <FirstName>. Now, if you wish to speak on other matters, we may do so. If not, I would ask that you leave my chambers...
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> Perhaps you are right, <FirstName>... We... we did not know each other well then... and it would be nice to confide my tale in someone else...
For, you see, my tale is closely tied to this ritual... and it is one that has followed me steps for so long now...

<StartAction>[Kara glances at the table full of ingredients, then back at you. She seems uneasy speaking on this matter further.]</Start> I... I am not sure I can trust you with such knowledge, <FirstName>...
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> I am sorry, <FirstName>... but I simply do not yet know you well enough to trust you so... Please, let us speak on another matter...
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> I suppose you do seem trustworthy enough... Very well, if you truly wish to know more about me, I shall tell you my tale, for it is closely tied to this ritual...

I suppose you may at that, <FirstName>. After all... it was you who aided me in retrieving the most important ingredient... <StartAction>[From the depths of her belt pouch, Kara produces the Bloodstone you helped her retrieve in Ghaarak.]</Start>
<StartAction>[Kara utters a brief incantation, then easily crushes the Bloodstone in her hand. A fine layer of red dust sprinkles across the liquid she has prepared in the vial before her...]</Start>
<StartAction>[Kara gives a small smile at your amazed expression.]</Start> I suppose you are curious as to what I am concocting here, and rightfully so...
This particular ritual is designed to aid me in stemming back a great evil which has haunted me all my life... and one that is growing stronger by the day...

I was born in Rhun, an ancient city on the outskirts of the Sharakhan Empire. While Rhun claims fealty to Emperor Rakha, all know it is simply a farce, for the city is ruled by one who bows to no other...
The Wytch of Rhun is her title, and she rules the city with an iron grip. For thousands of years, the line of Wytches have reigned over Rhun, and none dare oppose their might...
For the Wytches of Rhun are the chosen of Akhana, Goddess of Death, and their power is great. All who reside in Rhun live in fear, for even death cannot protect one from the Wytch's anger.

I suppose you are wondering how I know all of this, and rightfully so... I know this, for I am the daughter of the Wytch of Rhun... and with my lineage comes the touch of Akhana, one I will never fully escape from.

My sisters and I were raised in the Wytch's Hall, where the dreaded Disciples of Akhana trained and tested us, attempting to discover which among the Wytch's daughters possessed the strongest touch of Akhana.
My sisters were strong in Akhana's power, and lavished upon greatly for it. I, on the other hand, seemed free of the taint of Death, and as such, little heed was paid to me.

My place in the family was enough for me, however, for I had little liking for the dark practices of the Disciples of Akhana. Instead, I spent my days among the noble parties of the city, enjoying the wealth of my station.
So it may have continued, had fate not seen otherwise... I had fallen in love with a young noble man of the city, and we planned to be wed on the first day of spring.

My mother endorsed the wedding, for I believe she secretly wanted to be rid of me... her daughter who lacked the "touch." On the night of my wedding, however, something happened that would change my fate forever.
Akhana visited my mother in a dream, telling her that I was to be the Chosen, the next Wytch of Rhun when my mother departed this world forever...

The Wytch cannot deny the word of Akhana, and my mother ordered her Disciples to bring a halt to my wedding. Storming into the church, the foul servants of Akhana took both my groom and myself away screaming...
We were brought before my mother, and she ordered my groom to be sacrificed as a gift to Akhana. I was forced to watch, in horror and sadness, as my groom was burned alive...
I cursed my mother that night, and swore I would never serve Akhana's will. Her response was to turn me over to the care of the Disciples of Akhana... who tortured me endlessly for many months...

In the end, I was brought forth from the dungeons, claiming I had seen my destiny at Akhana's side. My mother was pleased, and I was sent to begin my training to one day take rule as the Wytch of Rhun.
But I had deceived them all, and when the chance presented itself, I slew my mentors, fleeing the city of Rhun. I swore never to return, and to this day, I have kept my oath.

My mother has constantly hunted me since then, sending her Disciples of Akhana after me time and again. Each time, I have eluded them, but there numbers have begun growing stronger... and another threat has arisen...

The touch of Akhana has begun to strengthen within me. I... I hear the voice of the Goddess of Death in my mind, I hear her bidding me to do her dark will... And... and sometimes I cannot fully resist it...
With nowhere left to turn, and the Disciples of Akhana always on my trail, I turned to the Empire for aid. And so I was brought here, to join the ranks of the ShadowGuard.

It has been a beneficial relationship, for the ShadowGuard have found good use for my talents in the dark arts, and in return, have given me the means to prepare this ritual... one which keeps Akhana's power over me at bay.

So, <FirstName>, this ritual is of great importance to me, for without it, I would become little more than a pawn to the Goddess of Death. Without it, I would cease to be free to live my own destiny...
<StartAction>[Kara smiles, but it is a sad smile.]</Start> And I am glad to have told it... Thank you, <FirstName>... it is good to have someone to speak to on this matter...
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_ST_1_MAIN" >>
<< Activates "N_TALK_SWITCH" if "N_MODULE_STAGE" is 1. >>

<StartAction>[Kara breathes heavily with the exertion of her fight against the Disciples of Akhana, but her eyes are clear as she looks up to you.]</Start> I... I thank you for your aid, <lad/lass>... I do not know if I could have staved them off alone...
Yes, and I apologize for that. Those men, the Disciples of Akhana, can be quite heavy handed in their tactics, and do not think twice about taking life in the name of the Goddess of Death...
Yes, and such would surely have been my fate if you had not been here to assist me. Know that you have my gratitude...
I must flee this place soon, for others of Ghasaran's ilk may be here in the city and this current reprieve will not last long... I fear Ghaarak is no longer safe for me.
As you wish, m'<lord/lady>. Know that you have my gratitude in driving off Ghasaran and his lackeys. Perhaps we may yet meet again, should the gods see fit for such...
No... no, I suppose you would not. Very well, then. We shall not delay this parting any more than we must...
I thank you, m'<lord/lady>, but some things are better to flee from than to fight. I am grateful for what aid you have already given me but I dare not ask for more...
<StartAction>[Kara's eyes dance nervously around the room.]</Start> There is truly no time for such a tale at the moment, m'<lord/lady>. I must make my escape before more of the Disciples find me!
For now, I bid you farewell, <lad/lass>. Who knows? Perhaps fate shall place our paths along the same road once more, but for the moment, I must flee the city before it is too late...
<StartAction>[Kara waves in farewell, and quickly exits the chamber, leaving you to ponder over these strange events...]</Start>
It looks like we have little choice but to fight these fiends now...
<StartAction>[You hear Ghasaran's voice booming behind you. A latch closes and you can hear his men barring the door from the inside so no one will interrupt.]</Start>
I knew you would lead us to the witch soon enough, <Race> <man/woman>! We have been closely watching you since our first meeting out in the streets...
<StartAction>[Kara scowls at Ghasaran.]</Start> I should have known that foul stench I smelled upon the air was you, Ghasaran... You don't intend to ever leave me in peace, do you...
<StartAction>[Ghasaran snickers.]</Start> There is nowhere left for you to go, witch! The time has come for you to face your punishment!

<StartAction>[Kara takes hold of your arm to steady herself, and you feel her hand shaking beneath her grasp.]</Start> I don't know exactly how we're going to get out of this one... These fellows are not ones to be trifled with...
You don't understand, do you? These men have no qualms as to killing you as well as me... Believe me, I know... You can either aid me, or you can die by my side...
<StartAction>[Kara shakes her head solemnly.]</Start> If you are not careful, <lad/lass>, your foolishness will cost you your life... but do as you wish. I shall not stand in your way...

<StartAction>[Kara leans in, whispering into your ear.]</Start> If you can distract Ghasaran for a moment, we may be able to surprise them with an attack... I'll use the Blood stone. Hopefully that will be enough...
Thanks... Good luck, <FirstName>... I will wait for the chance to pose itself, then I shall make my strike...
<StartAction>[Kara scowls at you.]</Start>Well, if you hadn't take the Bloodstone I may have been able to subdue them. But now? We are in for a struggle...
You... you fool! You led the Disciples of Akhana to me?! Do you have any idea what you have done?!
So what brings you back to my chambers, <lad/lass>? I would have thought our dealings were now finished...
Yes, well, I'm not up for much in the way of pleasantries, so please excuse me...
<StartAction>[Kara's eyes grow wide, and her face pales in fear.]</Start> Wh... what did these men look like, <lad/lass>? Tell me quickly!
<StartAction>[Though you did not think it possible, Kara's face grows even more pale.]</Start> The Disciples of Akhana! I... I must get out of here!
<StartAction>[Suddenly, Kara's eyes dart from your gaze to the door of her chamber. You turn to see the armored forms of the men seeking the Elven woman, and they appear none too happy...]</Start>
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_PREL_KARA_2" >>

<StartAction>[Kara Dy'nesh looks up at your approach. Her face is still pale from the exertion of her trance, though she is clearly in better condition than when you saw her last.]</Start> I sense the spirit has returned to the Underworld...
I am glad that spirit was able to find peace, and return to its proper place... I hope that my services were of aid to you as well...
Good luck to you in your travels, <lad/lass>... Perhaps we may yet meet again...
I hope you are quite happy with yourself, <lad/lass>! That Bloodstone was of great importance to me, and took me months to track down... Now I shall be forced to go through the whole process again!
Get out of my sight! I do not wish to speak to you further!
<StartAction>[Kara appears to be a bit weak in the knees from her possession by the spirit of Malgor, and wobbles unsteadily on her feet.]</Start>
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> <StartAction>[Even in her weakened state, Kara proves too fast for you.]</Start> Don't even think about it, <FirstName>!
<StartAction>[Success] [You easily snatch the Bloodstone from Kara's belt pouch, placing it quickly into your pack before she can fully recover.]</Start>
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> <StartAction>[Kara quickly grips the stone with both hands and twists her small frame away from you.]</Start> Don't even think about it, <FirstName>!
<StartAction>[Success] [Though Kara struggles momentarily, you easily pull the stone from her weakened grasp.]</Start>

<StartAction>[Kara accepts your offer for help with gratitude.]</Start> Thank you... It... it is not easy communicating with the dead in such a fashion... and I am afraid it will take me a while still to recover...
Well, good luck in your search, <lad/lass>. I hope my trance was of service to you, and should you need any further help, feel free to return to me here...
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> I will not risk my life for the safety of Nelgir. That merchant dog is getting only what he deserves!

<StartAction>[Success] [Kara's eyes become glassy as she looks at the bloodstone.]</Start> I feel terrible about what I have done. The havoc in the market is all my fault, but I know that if I relinquish this stone I will die.
I wish my life had not come to this... <StartAction>[Kara sobs.]</Start> I want to help, but I will not give up the stone, <FirstName>. I fear what may come if I am found without it.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> <StartAction>[Kara's eyes burn with rage.]</Start> You already stole the stone from me you deceitful worm! Now you ask for help!? Begone!
Well, yes... However, I need the stone for other purposes. I feel foolish bickering over this small stone but without it I am nearly defenseless.

<StartAction>[Kara seems surprised by your words.]</Start> Well, that would explain why the spirit has remained so long... I imagine a spirit murdered in such a fashion would certainly want to see to its vengeance...
<StartAction>[Kara frowns.]</Start> I've already told you, <lad/lass>, that's just not possible... I need the Bloodstone, and I cannot turn it over to you...
Well, then, I suppose you shall have to find some proof of Nelgir's guilt... Did the spirit mention anything that may be of aid?
Dark and full of a terrible stench... Perhaps a sewer of some sorts? It might be worth starting there, at least, and seeing what you may find...

<StartAction>[Kara seems surprised by your words.]</Start> Well, that would explain why the spirit has remained so long... I imagine a spirit murdered in such a fashion would certainly want to see to its vengeance...
<StartAction>[Kara frowns.]</Start> I've already told you, <lad/lass>, that's just not possible... I need the Bloodstone, and I cannot turn it over to you...
Well, then, I suppose you shall have to find some proof of Nelgir's guilt... Did the spirit mention anything that may be of aid?
Dark and full of a terrible stench... Perhaps a sewer of some sorts? It might be worth starting there, at least, and seeing what you may find...

Excellent work, <FirstName>! However, there is little I can do for Malgor now. You should take his body to the Imperial Guards. I'm certain that if this evidence is brought before officer Ganolin, the spirit's murderous son will be exposed.
Shall I enter my trance, and allow the spirit I summoned to speak through me? I am more than willing to do so, if we can yet resolve this affair peacefully...
<StartAction>[Kara appears quite uncomfortable with your question.]</Start> It... it was a gift I was born with... a gift... and a curse.
The blood of my family is strong with the power of Akhana, Goddess of Death, and I have always had a strong bond with the realm of the Underworld.

It is not a matter I wish to speak further on, at least not until I can trust you enough to call you a friend. For now, you need only know that I can aid you in finding a way to put this spirit to rest...

Through a ritual of the dead, I shall contact the spirit, allowing it to possess my body for a brief period of time. It will be able to speak through me, and thus explain its purpose for remaining here on the mortal plane.
As you wish. My offer shall remain open, so please return to me if you should decide differently.

<StartAction>[Kara slowly raises her hands and the room grows cold and dark. Her eyes to roll back in her head as she invokes an unnatural call.]</Start> Spirit of the dead, hear me! Speak through me, so that we may yet know your purpose!

<StartAction>[To your surprise, as the Elven woman's eyes roll back down into focus, they have taken on a milky white color. When Kara begins to speak once more, her voice has grown deep and unnatural...]</Start>
Who... who is it that calls me forth?! Your voice I hear, but my eyes cannot see... Speak your purpose, for in death my patience has grown thin!
Nelgir... Nelgir! I should have drowned that little brat at birth, and I would have too, had I known the depths of his treacherous little mind! Curses be upon that name!
So, Nelgir has sent you, has he? I should have known he would seek to rid himself of my presence, for the guilt must be more than his weak little mind can stand!
So be it, mortal! Hear my tale, and listen well, for within it lies the answer to breaking the spell which holds me in this realm...
I am the risen spirit of Malgor, once the most prominent gem trader throughout the Northern Reaches...

Then my life was snuffed from existence by the hand of my treacherous offspring, the weasel I named Nelgir! Stabbed in the dark for a small hoard of gems, that was my fate, all for the greed of my bastard son!
By the hand of this Elven witch have I been brought back to Abaran, and here I shall remain, until justice is served, or I am forced once more to depart!
If you wish for me to return to the Underworld from whence I came, bring the treacherous worm that is my son into the hands of justice!

Should you seek to bring justice against Nelgir, look for my body in the place where I fell... My memory is hazy with the fog of death, but I remember it to be a place of darkness and a terrible stench...

Now, the bonds which hold me to the body of this Elven witch grow weak, and I must depart... Remember my words well, young mortal! Only by giving me what I seek shall you rid this city of my spirit's presence!
<StartAction>[With a great howl, the spirit releases its possession of Kara's body, and she slumps forward weakly, then slowly rises...]</Start>

<StartAction>[The Elven maiden turns her dark green eyes to yours dangerously as you approach.]</Start> Who are you, <boy/girl>? I suggest you speak quickly, for I do not take kindly to strangers barging into my quarters unannounced.

<StartAction>[A dangerous glint sparkles in the woman's eyes, but she eases her stance a bit.]</Start> I shall forgive your tone for the moment, <lad/lass>, for I do not wish trouble during my stay here...
Perhaps we have gotten off on the wrong start. Please, allow me to introduce myself.
<StartAction>[The woman frowns at your reply, but seems to let the matter drop.]</Start> Not one for formalities, I see...

<StartAction>[At the mention of your name, the woman seems to relax a bit.]</Start> <FullName>, eh? I would have thought the <CUSTOM6001> of Okaris <LastName> would have better manners than this, but I shall forgive your actions... for now...

My name is Kara Dy'nesh, and I am a travelling priestess of the Northern Reaches on business here in Ghaarak. Now, I must ask that you tell me to what purpose you have barged into my quarters so rudely...

Theft? You accuse me of theft?! Nelgir sought to squeeze my purse dry for that utterly worthless Bloodstone, and you call me the thief?! I believe you have the circumstances reversed, my young friend...
In case you were unaware, bloodstones are a common sight along the roads to the north. They are considered no more then simple rocks in these parts.

<StartAction>[Kara relaxes a bit, but she still stands ready to defend herself.]</Start> The spirit still remains? That is most unusual, for the spell I used to summon it should have expired in but a moment.
<StartAction>[Placing her hand upon her chin, the Elven woman appears deep in thought.]</Start> If my spell is no longer holding the spirit here... It must be bound to this plane by its own will.

<StartAction>[Kara looks back at you once more.]</Start> Quite simply, it's a re-agent required for dispelling spirits and other... more powerful spells. I usually keep a number of these rocks on my person.
Unfortunately the road to Ghaarak is a long and dangerous one. During the trek here I used up my bloodstone supply. When I saw Nelgir's stand I hoped to restock.
The fool was charging three hundred gold pieces for a simple red rock! No right-minded merchant would charge more then a single gold piece for a bloodstone! I do not regret the theft!
The spell I used was not one of any direct danger to Nelgir, more of a ruse to distract him while I made my escape... I do not believe the spirit will cause him any bodily harm.
<StartAction>[Kara appears to consider your words carefully.]</Start> Perhaps you are right... I... I did not mean to cause Nelgir any permanent harm, but I need this stone badly...

I cannot return the Bloodstone to Nelgir, for it is of great importance to me. Despite what that fool may claim, it is of very little worth. Trust me, the loss of such a gem will not hurt his purse in the least...
But I suppose you are right... I have caused more havoc than I meant to. I truly did not believe that the summoning spell would last as it did.

For a spirit to remain in the mortal realm for so long, it must have some strong purpose tying it here. If you like, I can attempt to contact the spirit through a trance, allowing it to use my body to communicate with you.

Perhaps then you could learn to what purpose the spirit remains tied to this realm, and discover a way to dispel it. That would free Nelgir of its presence, and allow me to keep the Bloodstone I so desperately need.
<StartAction>[An awkward silence descends, broken finally by a stifled titter from Kara. No longer able to contain herself, she breaks into a forlorn giggle.]</Start>
Oh my, I have made a bad first impression, haven't I? Stealing gems, summoning spirits, and now a good tongue-lashing besides. Please, accept my apologies and allow me to explain...
[The Elven woman struggles in vain against Nelgir's grip.] Let me go, or you shall learn to regret it!
Can't you see I'm a bit busy here, <lad/lass>? If you must distract someone, try this wretched merchant, could you?

<StartAction>[Kara looks towards you with loathing in her eyes, though there is a great weariness there as well.]</Start> You... you treacherous little worm! You... you've taken my Bloodstone, after... after I tried to make peace with you!

<StartAction>[Kara moves as though to strike against you, but her legs are still weak from her trance, and she stumbles to the ground.]</Start> A curse upon you, <lad/lass>! May you rot in the hells for what you have done!
<StartAction>[Kara fumes but seems to realize she has little choice.]</Start> As you may have noticed by now, I have certain abilities to communicate with those beyond the veil of death.

My skills have always been sought after by evil groups. My current pursuers are a band of dark priests who fear and desire my power. They consider me a heretic of sorts... I have been fleeing them for the last several weeks.

The Bloodstones help me defend myself against these priests. More importantly, they may help me put the pursuit to rest and allow me to prove my innocence... Otherwise, I will likely be... disposed of.

You are a fool! Time is short and you would undo all the work that I have done? <StartAction>[Kara crumples to the ground in despair, her limbs, already weakened by the trance, now giving out on her completely.]</Start>

<StartAction>[Kara reaches out and reclaims the Bloodstone, her eyes searching your face for signs of further betrayal.]</Start> You made a wise decision, my friend. I am not one to let the dead lie nor the living stand if they oppose me...

Comment.value: Default dialogue when the henchman is a member of the player's party.

value.0: What may I do for you, <FirstName>?
As you wish, <FirstName>.

It is a painful and draining experience to summon forth a dweller of the Underworld, <FirstName>. I can do as you ask, but I will be required to rest afterwards if I am to accomplish such a feat again.
Are you sure you still wish for me to do this?
As you wish, <FirstName>.
Very well... <StartAction>[The pupils of Kara's eyes take on a whitish glow as she enters a deep trance to summon forth an undead minion...]</Start>
Akhana, Mistress of the Night, heed my call! I beg thee lend thy mortal servant aid! <StartAction>[A hazy cloud of smoke gathers around Kara, and you see a dark spectre rise from its midst.]</Start>
Daughter of Dy'nesh, Akhana answers thy call! My services shall be at thy command...
<StartAction>[You notice Kara's face has lost all its color, and her breathing seems a bit short.]</Start> It is done... <FirstName>. This spirit shall aid us in our journey...
As you wish, <FirstName>.
I always like to prepare for a tough fight with my magic. So what should I do?
Wise of you to plan ahead. Thanks for reminding me.
No, I think I'm all set for now, thank you very much.
Cute little friend, isn't it? And now ready for battle.
Your cute pet already has all the protections I can offer.
Where did this creature come from anyway? I have never seen anything like it. Anyhow, it's now as ready for battle as it'll ever be?
This "friend" of yours already has all the protections I can offer.
Cute little friend, isn't it? And now ready for battle.
Your cute little pet already has all the protections I can offer.
I don't think I have the appropriate spells ready for that. Should we rest?
You're all set, my dear <FirstName>!
You already have all the protections I can offer.
No one here needs the protections I've got ready.
Sorry: I've done all I can.
As you wish, <FirstName>.
If you feel such is necessary, <FirstName>, then so be it. I shall await you here should you require my services once more.
Very well, then, <FirstName>. I shall stay by your side for the time being.
Very well, <FirstName>. I shall go for now. Feel free to seek me out should you need my assistance at a later time.
My services are at your command, <FirstName>.
Very well, <FirstName>.
Very well, <FirstName>.
I will try to heal you even if I am being attacked at close range.
Very well, I will heal you only if I am not in hand-to-hand combat.
As you wish.
Why, what is the matter with what I'm doing now?
Very well, but I will still refrain from healing you if I am in close-range combat.
Very well, I will both cast attack spells and heal you whenver necessary.
Very well, I will neither cast attack spells nor heal you if I'm in close-range combat.
